The tree in the waves copies the window frames, rails, decorative elements of the door, cuckoo and rails.
The Batlló House, which stands in the Eixample district on the busy Passeig de Grácia 43 shopping street, was rebuilt by the architect Emilio Sala Cortese in 1877.
The reconstruction took place for two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, the rich industrialist Josep Batlló, originally insisted on demolishing an old building and building a completely new one, but soon he accepted Gaudí's idea for an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
The Casa Batlló Chinahouse but Antoni Gaudí did not design himself.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol cooperated with him.
