In the work of Gaud, he did not respect the building regulations at that time and did not allow himself to be bound by them.
At the beginning of the building, though he obtained a building permit from the city, the above data on the planned reconstruction were so vague that two years later, the city council was reinstated and asked for a remedy.
For example, the council did not mind that the construction involved the pillars and the public pavement.
There has never been a correction, on the contrary: only 15 days after the call of the city part, Josep Batlló requested (and successfully obtained) permission to rent two top floors of the building.
